county: Yorkshire West Riding and Yorkshire North Riding
comments:
On 30.9.1895 the Yorkshire North Riding part of the parish of 
    Lower Dunsforth became part of Yorkshire West Riding, so that thereafter Lower 
    Dunsforth was wholly in Yorkshire West Riding. See also Table 2, notes (b) and 
    (k).

On 1.4.1895 the part in Yorkshire West Riding was transfererd 
    to Yorkshire North Riding, so that thereafter Milby was entirely in 
    Yorkshire North Riding. See Table 2, notes (c) and (i).

Abolished 1.4.1938 and added to the parish of Boroughbridge. 
    See also Table 2, note (b).

county: Yorkshire West Riding and Yorkshire North Riding
comments:
On 30.9.1895 the Yorkshire North Riding part of the parish of 
    Upper Dunsforth with Branton Green became part of Yorkshire West Riding, so 
    that thereafter Upper Dunsforth with Branton Green was wholly in Yorkshire West 
    Riding. See also Table 2, notes (b) and (k).
